<plot>From 1854 to 1861, the eyes of the nation were on Kansas Territory. Two sides emerged, intent on extending or eliminating the spread of slavery. Amidst this historical backdrop, passionate individuals like John Brown would arise as the voice of a new land. Before Kansas gained statehood in 1861, hundreds would die - the outcome defining a state, and a nation.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?614294</url></doc>
